        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 1:00PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 100 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles southwest of Hobson, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sapphire Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
